@endnode
@node minefield
@{b}
Minefield
@{ub}
Oops! A careless Worm stacked to many mines in the store room and then left 
the door open. One of the frequent explosions in Wormville shook the mines 
loose and scattered them all over the town. The Worm in question was quickly
executed by a Worm from an opposing tribe. His own tribe felt it only right 
to retaliate, and war ensued. The only problem was that noone knew which of
the mines were armed...
@endnode
@node dentures
@{b}
Dentures
@{ub}
This level is intended to promote good dental hygine and the termination
with extreme prejudice of other Worm teams. Get to it!
@endnode
@node sandstone
@{b}
Sandstone
@{ub}
When the Worms discovered a mysterious group of floating Sandstone bricks
and columns, there was only one thing to do... Fight over them!
@endnode
@node moonbases
@{b}
Moonbase/Moonbase 2
@{ub}
Humans finally developed the technology to populate the moon. They set 
about building two Moonbases in the Sea of Tranquility, one in a convenient
crater, and one on the site of a mysterious black monolith...

The monolith obviously came under a great deal of study, as scientists
tried to discover what it was, and what purpose it served. However, their
research didn't slow the production of the two Moonbases. Construction was
well under way.

If the scientists had known how, they would have discovered that the
monoltih was, in fact, a warning to stop people populating the moon, because
it was the resting place of a species of giant Worms. These Worms had been
entombed in the moon as they were a war-like race whose battles had 
destroyed many planets. Any construction work could rouse them from their
slumber.

The humans didn't know this, and so were very surprised when the ground
around their moonbases suddenly sprouted giant Worms.

The humans quickly evacuated the moon, leaving the two moonbases as 
playgrounds for the Worms as they began again their centuries-old war...

(See also @{"Space" link space} and @{"Mars" link mars})
@endnode
@node space
@{b}
Space
@{ub}
The Moon-worms had been fighting non-stop for three years. The people of
Earth had at first found this entertaining, and the popular show Moon-worm
Battles had finally knocked Gladiators 2099 off the top of the ratings
charts.

However, any fall-out or near misses on the moon were automatically drawn 
towards the largest nearby centre of gravity - the Earth. Mass destruction
ensued as Worm missiles rained down upon the hapless humans.

Eventually, the people of earth had had enough. They flew a huge space-ship 
to the moon and tempted the Worms aboard using a huge inflatable dummy of
Phil Collins. When all the Worms were aboard they fired the ship off into
space.

Unfortunately, the Worms didn't stop fighting just because they were on a
space-ship - in fact, if anything they became angrier and fought more
violently, causing the ship to veer off course and break down just a few
hundred thousand miles from Mars.

The Worms abandoned the ship and continued the battle in the depths of
space...

(See also @{"Moonbase/Moonbase2" link moonbases} and @{"Mars" link mars})
@endnode
@node mars
@{b}
Mars
@{ub}
Finally, the Moon-worms made it to the planet Mars having hitched a lift off
a passing flying saucer. To their surprise (if, indeed, they had emotions) 
they realised that they'd come across an ancient Martian settlement. This
was a cause for great celebration ie. shooting each other...

(See also @{"Moonbase/Moonbase2" link moonbases} and @{"Space" link space})
@endnode
@node heads
@{b}
Heads
@{ub}
This landscape was built in a distant district of Wormville by Worms angry
at years of being stepped on and pulled apart by small children. The
numerous models of human heads dotted about are there to be destroyed...
especially if there's an opposition Worm on them...
@endnode
@node slippyrock
@{b}
Slippyrock
@{ub}
It was a bad day in Wormville. A Worm had been sent to fetch a bucket of
oil to lubricate the firing mechanisms on the rocket launchers and had 
spilled the oil all over the place, rendering even rocks as slippy as ice.
So, not only was there a pitched battle, the Worms also had to put up with
their rocket launchers squeaking!
@endnode
node discs
@{b}
Discs
@{ub}
The Worms had run out of blank discs, and so a great meeting was called.

The Worms tribes met in the centre of Wormville, and, after many long 
minutes of discussion, came to the conclusion that if there was a gnome
that stole all the Pencils, there was probably a gnome that stole all of the
blank discs.

They were right, but it was just a coincidence.

And so after the usual cycle of threats, cajoling, more threats, pleas, even 
more threats, and the waving of a huge wand, the Worms found themselves in
a huge place full of blank discs. And so, a huge battle ensued...
@endnode
@node cake
@{b}
Cake
@{ub}
It was the birthday of Mark Hamill Worm. The Worms tribes had worked 
together on a huge chocolate cake, surprising themselves - they weren't
used to cooperating (although a record number of Worms had died deciding
what flavour the cake should be). Mark Hamill Worm was presented the cake, 
which marked the passing of his fourth birthday, and the Worms tribes 
considered that this celebration might actually usher in a new period of
peace and tranquility.

So happy were the Worms that they failed to notice that one of the four 
candles adorning the cake was much larger than the rest. And it was fizzing
alarmingly. And it had TNT written on it.

The TNT exploded, taking Mark Hamill Worm to a Better Place (TM), and 
covering the entire of Wormville in sticky chocolate cake. The great era of
peace and tranquility was forgotten in favour of a new era of war and mass 
destruction, and the Worms found that they were much happier this way. So 
that was alright.
@endnode
@node knights
@{b}
Knights
@{ub}
The Worm Council decided to plant a memorial garden in honour of all the 
Worms who had fallen in combat over the years. Unfortunately, they agreed
to let Thaddeus P. Worm add a serum to the gladioli seeds to promote rapid 
growth. Instead of gladioli, the Worms found Knights in shining armour
sprouting up all over the place. There was only one thing to do about this
problem - have a great big barney!
@endnode
@node flat
@{b}
Flat
@{ub}
A further training ground for young Worms. All the Worms are on one level
which isn't too wide. There's no scenery to hide behind. Total destruction
is often the result of a training session here!

(See also @{"Toyland" link toyland} and @{"Metal" link metal})
@endnode
@node signs
@{b}
Signs
@{ub}
The Worms Tribes were off on their annual holiday to blow each other up in 
Bognor Regis. Unfortunately, they should have taken a left at Alberquerque,
and instead ended up in Lime Regis. Obviously this wouldn't do, and so, 
after the total obliteration of the Worm tribe who was looking after the 
map, the Worms preceded to the local information office.

The people working in the information office were not too pleased to be 
confronted by a large group of unhappy, gun-toting Worms, and it looked as 
though the information office would be blown off the face of the planet,
but then one bright young desk clerk had the brainwave of tempting all of 
the Worms into the back yard where they stored all of the old signs. The
Worms became lost amongst the signs, and so, to ease their frustration, they
decided to kill each other...
@endnode
