@node sheep
@{b}
Secret Sheep Mode!
@{ub}
To enter the Sheep mode, type "TOTAL WORMAGE" while on the title screen.
The screen will change colour, and the game will announce that you've 
entered Sheep Mode. You now have access to all of the special weapons (such
as Sheep, Banana Bombs and the Minigun) and you can alter how many you get 
on the appropriate options screen.
@endnode
@node prod
@{b}
Secret Prod Move
@{ub}
To activate the secret Prod move, stand your worm next to an opposing worm
and, using the cursor keys, press away, away, towards, towards. This will 
cause your worm to push the enemy. If you're at the top of a slope on an icy 
landscape this move can be very useful!
@endnode
@node custom
@{b}
Altering Custom Level Attributes
@{ub}
If you've created a custom level, you'll know you have to save it as

 Levelname.WRM

However, you can change the gravity and friction, and the colour of the sea,
on any level by saving it as

 Levelname.abxy.WRM

Replace a and b with a number from 1 to 5. The letter a represents gravity,
and b represents friction. Therefore, a level saved as

 Levelname.15xy.WRM 

would have low gravity and high friction.

The letters x and y should also be replaced by numbers from 1 to 5, and 
control the colour of the sea. Experiment with these to get results you like!
@endnode
@node comments
@{b}
Creating Level Comments
@{ub}
When you play a regular game of worms, don't you find those random comments
the computer throws up before each level starts hilarious? And don't you just 
wish that you could do them too? Well, now you can!

While in Workbench, insert your level disk. The art program you use to 
create the levels should have saved them with an icon. Click on this once
and then select Information or Info from the pull-down menus.

When the information screen has loaded, simply write your message in the 
Comments box. Your message should be no longer than 40 characters long.
Then, just save the information and everything will work. The next time you
load your custom level in worms your witty message will appear!
@endnode
